node.text:
Here’s the truth about “FDA Approved”:

There’s a BIG misconception that the FDA diligently reviews and approves new ingredients before we start eating them. 

Sadly this isn’t the case. 

New ingredients are usually approved by the food manufacturer themselves, and NOT by the FDA. 

All an ingredient manufacturer has to do is HIRE THEIR OWN EXPERTS to claim it’s safe. This is the green light to start adding it to food products.

Several “FDA Approved” products have been yanked from the shelves after they were found to be downright dangerous. 

But this doesn’t happen overnight. 

History shows that it takes YEARS before the FDA acts and removes harmful products from the market. 

Something very serious needs to happen – like deaths – before the FDA takes action. And even then, they may not.

Remember how Johnson & Johnson’s talc powder was recently removed from the shelves after slews of cancer claims and cover-ups by the company?

Well, the FDA didn’t ban it. 

J&J voluntarily decided to stop selling it to stop lawsuits from piling up.

Meanwhile, this controversial ingredient is banned in Europe. 

This just goes to show how little the FDA has done to protect our health. 

Tag your friends below to spread the word!

Even though we’ve made tremendous progress…the truth is that big companies just don’t change fast enough.

I believe we deserve to live in a world where our products can be made without weird – and nasty – ingredients.

Is that too much to ask?

Apparently so. Because we are so far away it’s crazy.

So, I decided to take matters into my own hands.

I launched @truvani and we have one main goal: eliminate nasty ingredients from all daily-use products.

We started with supplements. Now we are creating personal care products. 

Visit Truvani.com to learn more.

I know you’ll like them. And when you see the ingredient labels, you’ll LOVE THEM.

node.text:
When I first shared this graphic a few months ago, Ghirardelli was using the risky ingredient TBHQ in their chocolate squares. Well, I’m excited to let you know that they have quietly replaced TBHQ with “extracts of oregano, flaxseed, plum, and green tea”. Swipe left to see the new ingredient list.

Yeah! Thank you to everyone in the #FoodBabeArmy who has asked these companies to remove TBHQ. 

This is one ingredient that we need out of our food ASAP.

TBHQ is a synthetic preservative still found in many of the most popular foods here in America…like Pop Tarts, Cheez-it Crackers, and Reese’s Peanut Butter Cups. Foods that many children eat often!

A peer-reviewed study by the Environmental Working Group found TBHQ may harm the immune system.

TBHQ has already been shown to worsen flu symptoms and is linked to other health issues, such as increasing the risk of food allergies to nuts, milk, eggs, wheat, and shellfish.

Although the FDA allows food companies to use this controversial preservative, it’s banned in some other countries, and you rarely see it used in Europe.

When new research comes out like this, the FDA does nothing! They don’t reevaluate or pull ingredients from our food supply. 

It’s up to us...

It’s up to us to protect ourselves by refusing to buy products with TBHQ on the ingredient list and demanding that these companies stop using potentially harmful substances. 

Both Chick-Fil-A and McDonald’s used to use TBHQ in their food - but after customers raised concerns they both ditched it completely. Now Ghirardelli has gotten on board too. 

Let’s get everyone else to do the same! 

Please share this post! #FoodBabeArmy

Subscribe for updates: FoodBabe.com/subscribe

The fast food industry has mastered the ART OF ADDICTION. 

With chemicals like MSG and Natural Flavors they are able to hijack your taste buds so that you can’t stop eating their food and keep coming back for more. 

Almost every fast food is packed with Refined Flour or Sugar, which are some of the most addicting and damaging ingredients in processed food.

Once they’ve got you hooked on their nutritionless dead food, you’ll keep coming back. Next thing you know, you’re eating copious amounts of unhealthy ingredients that destroy your health and weight over time.

It’s hard to break the cycle!

When I was a child my favorite fast food place was Burger King.

While I’m writing this, I remember the taste so vividly even though I haven’t eaten it in over a decade. I can still smell it and my mouth waters when I think about it. 

It took me years to figure out how to break free from addictive fast food like this, and I want to help you do the same. 

Let’s break their control together.

You’ll find everything you need in Food Babe Kitchen (link in my bio!)

This book will help you replace all that addicting, fast, processed, and boxed food with fresh, real food. 

There are even recipes for a “Chick-Fil-A”, my favorite burgers, fries, and Homemade Doritos! 

Check it out at the link in my bio.

node.text:
Watch out for this ingredient in “low carb” and “zero sugar” products. You’ll also find sucralose in hundreds of products like yogurts, breads, juices, and drinks. So keep your eyes peeled for it. 

This artificial sweetener is made in a laboratory by reacting sugar with chlorine. 

✔️In 2016, researchers at an independent laboratory found that Sucralose caused leukemia and related blood cancers in male mice who were exposed to this ingredient throughout their lives. 

✔️Other studies have found that Sucralose changes the microbiome and enzymes in your gut - which can have negative effects on your blood sugar and metabolism. 

✔️Although they have no calories, artificial sweeteners have been shown to contribute to weight gain by encouraging sugar cravings. So, it might actually help you gain weight - not lose it. 

This is why a lot of people never reach their full health potential or weight loss goals, because they are constantly being pushed around by these chemical artificial sweeteners that trick the brain and body.

Please share to warn your friends about this sneaky ingredient! 

Subscribe to learn the truth about your food: FoodBabe.com/subscribe

node.text:
Be wary of non-dairy milks that are not certified organic. Here’s why:

Non-organic oats and non-organic almonds are both commonly sprayed with toxic chemicals like Roundup, which is known to cause cancer. The toxic fumigant Propylene Oxide (PPO) can be sprayed on non-organic almonds to “pasteurize” them. The National Toxicology Program rates PPO as “reasonably anticipated to be a human carcinogen.” Roundup and PPO are both banned on organic crops.

Even some organic versions are unhealthy. Watch out for added sugar, natural flavors, and unnecessary “gums”.

Some of the best organic brands are MALK, Three Trees, New Barn, Whole Foods 365 Organic, Thrive Market, Simple Truth Organic, Oatsome, and Native Forest or Natural Value Coconut Milk (canned). 

Ultimately, the best is homemade. Swipe left for 5 easy recipes!

If you’re making your own...

✔️ Choose raw organic nuts if possible for the most health benefits. 

✔️ For each of these recipes, they should be strained with a fine mesh strainer or nut milk bag after blending. 

✔️ To add a bit of sweetness, you could add one date before blending or 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract (or both!) 

✔️ They will last up to 4-5 days in the refrigerator or could even be frozen if desired to last longer if you want to make a big batch.

Tag your friends below to share these recipes.

Recent studies show that 70% of our immune system is in the gut. This means when our gut is healthy, we are too.

What you eat is the most important factor affecting your gut health (Swipe left to see more). 

In our over-sanitized modern world, most of us aren’t exposed to very much good bacteria, and this can be a problem. Most of our food has been pasteurized, irradiated, or chemically treated to kill bugs – but this also kills the good stuff. Our soil is depleted of good bacteria with the overuse of synthetic pesticides and other chemical contamination.

Then it’s processed and stripped of all nutrients and fiber, flavored with fake flavors, sweetened with white sugar or artificial sweeteners (which are known to alter good bacteria). Stop the madness! 

One thing we’re all responsible for is our own health. It’s not always easy to make the right decisions, but the payoff can be HUGE.

Some of the things I do each day to support my health: 

✔️ Eating lots of fruits and vegetables – I love eating fruit instead of sugar-filled snacks to curb my sweet tooth.

✔️ Taking my immune-support supplements religiously (like Probiotics, Vitamin D and Vitamin C).

✔️ Washing my hands every chance I get with basic natural soap (not Clorox wipes) 

✔️ Getting movement everyday, even if it’s just a walk to the neighborhood playground

✔️ Prioritize my sleep - This can be difficult with a baby, but I’m doing my best! 

✔️ Eating fermented foods like kimchi and homemade pickles

✔️ Avoiding white sugar as much as possible. 

✔️ Drinking green drinks every chance I get.

What are you doing each day to support your health? Tell me in the comments below!

You do not have to be blindly guided by Big Food and their million dollar marketing campaigns.

The food industry tries to lead us like sheep into eating processed, fake, chemical-filled foods. Big Food does not want us to pay any attention to ingredients, and don’t care what those ingredients are doing to our health.

We can’t control what they are doing to our food, but we can control what we put in our mouth.

Take control of your food by reading ingredient lists. Don’t just read the front of the package. Flip it over to see what it’s really made of. 

Look for the certified organic label too, as this will help you avoid GMO ingredients and synthetic pesticides. 

Food Babe Kitchen contains a detailed grocery shopping guide that takes you down every aisle of the grocery store, showing what exactly to look for on an ingredient list. This is the next best thing to bringing me grocery shopping with you!
